explanation: This solution uses a stack to reverse the strings in each pair of matching parentheses. It iterates through the input string, pushing characters onto the stack. When it encounters a closing parenthesis, it pops characters from the stack until it finds the corresponding opening parenthesis, then reverses the popped characters and pushes them back onto the stack. Finally, it constructs the result string by popping characters from the stack in reverse order.

